Feedback: Please provide general feedback on your experience with Cory. In particular, whether you feel that Cory was helpful or what he had trouble handling (2 sentences or more if you'd like).
Recommendation_1: Would you recommend Cory to a friend who wants to know more about COVID-19 and/or restrictions?

Feedback: I though Cory was helpful overall. Loved the links that allowed me to access additional information from reputable sites and also the question suggestions that it provided. The answers were simple and easy to read. However I found that access to information about interstate travel was limited particularly in regards to isolation and costs associated with it in other states. Not quite sure whether all info was up to date based on new restrictions that have come in overnight too (I could be wrong about that though). I found I was getting the same answers for very different questions but it still provided some great help in regards to information on mental health.
Cory was definitely helpful but in some of the questions, cory’s answer was not relevant to some of the questions. I would like Cory to answer in yes or no format too.

Cory was definitely helpful and I can see him being extremely useful for a lot of people who want urgent or fast information. Sometimes I got a little bit impatient waiting for him to finish answering a question as he sends quite a few messages for some questions and sometimes the messages aren’t completely necessary. But I do like the way some of the messages bring about a sense of empathy, like “I’m sorry to hear you’re experiencing symptoms” etc. I found that Cory gave different answers to the same question depending on what I referred to the virus as, e.g to the question about “what are the symptoms” he gave a different answer when I used the word coronavirus, to COVID and an even different answer for COVID-19 (the best answer was when I used COVID, and he sent a photo of the symptoms and explained to get tested. I think it would be good if he gave the response for all of the possible variations of the virus name, since different people will refer to it in different ways. Overall it was a really great and pleasant experience, and I think Cory could help a lot of people!
